<paragraph blockId="4.[151,638,1332,1619]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">
This species is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[440,514,1359,1380]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Mexico</collectingRegion>
in the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[180,255,1385,1406]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[267,335,1385,1406]" country="Mexico" name="Puebla" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Puebla</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[391,477,1385,1406]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
(Foley and Ivie 2008; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baselga, A. &amp; Recuero, G." box="[214,408,1411,1433]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" pagination="5060 - 5073" refId="ref3648" refString="Baselga, A., E. Recuero, G. Parra-Olea, and M. Garc'ia Par'is. 2011. Phylogenetic patterns in zopherine beetles are related to ecological niche width and dispersal limitation. Molecular Ecology 20: 5060 - 5073." type="journal article" year="2011">
Baselga 
<emphasis box="[298,349,1411,1433]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). We add the following record: “ 
<collectingCountry box="[247,346,1439,1460]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">MEXICO</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[364,453,1439,1460]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
, Tlaquilpa, Vista Hermosa, 
<date box="[251,357,1465,1486]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" value="2013-05-11">11-V-2013</date>
, 
<quantity box="[367,449,1465,1486]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4899999999999998" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" unit="m" value="2490.0">2,490 m</quantity>
, pine-oak forest, L. Delgado, E. Mora-A. cols.” (
<specimenCount box="[434,467,1491,1513]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" type="male">1 ♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount box="[478,510,1491,1513]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
, IEXA). The record from Refugio in the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[553,638,1518,1539]" country="Mexico" name="Durango" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Durango</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Champion, G. C." box="[158,321,1545,1566]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" pagination="477 - 524" refId="ref3832" refString="Champion, G. C. 1892. Supplement to Heteromera [pp. 477 - 524]. In: Biologia Centrali-Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. IV, Part 1 (F. D. Godman and O. Salvin, editors). Porter, London, UK." type="book chapter" year="1892">Champion 1892</bibRefCitation>
) needs confirmation due to its remoteness from the other states and the lack of intermediate records.
</paragraph>
